Text.SourceString: Hello to you too! I’m <NPCName>Macy</>.//<portrait=normal>Where are you visiting from? It’s nice to finally have a tourist in town.

Oh! You just moved to Coral Island?//<portrait=normal>That’s amazing, welcome, and confusing. Why? Well, I hope you’re getting around all right.//Coral Island is kind of big, so getting your bearings can be pretty hard at first.
You’ll get used to it in no time. I have no doubt.
I took pictures of the recycling center.//<portrait=happy>I want to document its stages and call the series <Italic>The Mess We Caused.</>
I have a picture of the recycling center when it was half empty, if you want to check it out.
I took pictures of the recycling center.//<portrait=happy>I want to document its stages and call the series <Italic>The Mess We Caused.</>
I have a picture of the recycling center when it was half empty, if you want to check it out.
I saw you clearing up debris on the lot near <NPCName>Erika</>'s house last week, and I called out to you.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think you heard me, though… Unless…
Oh well. You seemed busy that day.
Living at the inn really limits the gardening I can do.//I want to plant cauliflower, okra, and all kinds of vegetables.
No fruit, though.//<portrait=concerned>It requires a lot more space, right? I don’t think I’m ready for that much commitment.
Living at the inn really limits the gardening I can do.//I want to plant cauliflower, okra, and all kinds of vegetables.
No fruit, though.//<portrait=concerned>It requires a lot more space, right? I don’t think I’m ready for that much commitment.
What pictures sell the best? Oh, easy! People eat beach stuff right up. It’s the easiest money I’ve ever made!
I’m a sucker for nature panoramas. There’s always so much to take in! So much to share.
I’m not a morning person.//According to a study I read years ago, my chronotype means that my most efficient work hours are after 11 am.//<portrait=normal>Which I feel is very true.
If I eat too much in the morning, I feel nauseated all day! So I just grab coffee and bread before I head out.
I’m collecting my thoughts. Hmm…//What is it?
I’ve sold tons of <NPCName>Stephen</> pics! He’s a real champ about it. Always photo ready!
<PlayerName>$player</>? Are you okay?
You seem distraught. If there’s anything you want to say, please feel free to say it.
I get bored quickly… I play video games when I’m tired of editing pictures…//<portrait=happy>Then, if I’m still bored, I watch other people playing video games.
I don’t know what to tell you.//I guess it’s just interesting to watch people play games.
There are a lot of picturesque spots here. Um…
So usually, I take pictures, then submit them online for licensing.//People then buy the right to use my image through a third party…//<portrait=happy>This website where I submit my photographs.
I’m sure you’ve heard of the company, Pletty Inc.?//<portrait=happy>Yeah, that’s the site that sells my photographs.
I’ve sold plenty of <NPCName>Stephen</>'s pictures, titled “Lobster,” “Cute Lobster,” “Lobster Day Out,” “Sea Life.”//<portrait=normal>Umm… What else… What else?
I need to concentrate.
May I suggest you go back to work? So I can go back to focusing.
You can try going to the library. Or meditation, maybe.
I don’t like the rain. I usually spend rainy days editing pictures at the library and just play video games in my room all night.
Rain doesn’t seem to bother you, though, huh?
<NPCName>Stephen</>'s doing well today, thanks for asking.//<portrait=happy>What about you, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Game streaming seems like a fun thing to do!//<portrait=normal>But I can’t see myself doing that. I don’t feel comfortable being the center of attention.
Maybe if I get over that, I might just start streaming.//<portrait=blushing>He-he. I doubt it, though. I like being in the shadows too much.
Game streaming seems like a fun thing to do!//<portrait=normal>But I can’t see myself doing that. I don’t feel comfortable being the center of attention.
Maybe if I get over that, I might just start streaming.//<portrait=blushing>He-he. I doubt it, though. I like being in the shadows too much.
Saturday evenings? I spend them at the Tavern.//I don’t have a set schedule during the week… I usually just let the camera take me wherever.
I prefer to be behind the camera.//<portrait=happy>Oh, don’t worry too much about me! I think I’m an okay-looking and interesting gal.//<portrait=normal>I just don’t like being photographed.
The spotlight makes me nervous.

I call my parents every week to let them know I’m still <Italic>alive</>.//<portrait=happy>Ha! No joke. If I didn’t, they’d throw a tantrum like you wouldn’t believe! Drama monarchs…//<portrait=blushing>Love them, though.
I’m secretly relieved when my friends cancel plans. Socializing is exhausting sometimes.//<portrait=normal>Keep it between us, okay?
The mess is what’s making my room feel dirty. But in all seriousness, it actually isn’t. I’d say it’s immaculate.
I scrub the floor with disinfectant. You could eat off it if you wanted to… Don’t, though.
I think I might be overcompensating with all the cleaning.

Do you think it’s because I’m covered in dirt a lot? I always have this icky feeling that my room never feels clean, you know?//So I scrub and scrub and scrub… I don’t know if I’m making a lot of sense right now.
Favorite video game genre? Hmm… Hard question. I like action-adventure video games.//<portrait=happy>They let me travel to a different world whenever I want.
It’s escapism, so to speak.//<portrait=happy>Even if you have a great life, it’s still fun to explore the underworld or the galaxy sometimes, don’t you think?
I miss my family sometimes. My mom more than my dad, ha ha…//I love them both, though. Just…different connections.//You know?
<NPCName>Luke</> hired me to take some pictures of the vineyard one time, and I fell in love with it.//<portrait=happy>It’s just so beautiful.
I bet your farm would be great to photograph!//<portrait=happy>Maybe when I have the time, I can stop by and take pictures of you in action.
I only take selfies for my parents when they want “evidence” of my travels.
I learned photography from my mom. Why?
No, she isn’t a pro. She just always takes the family pictures.//Weddings, birthday parties, trips to the zoo, first time walking, first haircut… You name it, she’s snapped it.
Pizza? Oh yeah. I love it!//<portrait=normal>It’s delicious. You can have cheese, vegetables… Mmm! Yummy.
I love taking pictures of nature and its ever-changing character.//It shows us a new face every day.
My parents got me a TV as a gift. Can you believe it?//<portrait=normal>They know I like video games, and they knew I could use a new one. Sweet, isn’t it?
Hmm… Where should I take <NPCName>Stephen</>, you think?
Umm… It has to be close to the sea, though.//<portrait=normal>The lake is out of the question. I don’t think he’d be too happy with fresh water.
You go to the cavern a lot, don’t you? I always see you there.
Don’t worry! I’m not stalking you. Ha!//<portrait=normal>I go to the forest a lot too. It’s a great place to take pictures.
The girls at the inn always suggest getting dinner together.//Little things like that make me feel right at home.
I consider them family.
I noticed <NPCName>Eva</> likes to sew all kinds of clothes. She’s very skilled with her hands.//<portrait=happy>It’s so cool!
I notice that different flowers bloom each season.//It's hard to pick a favorite with that many options.
But keep an eye out for flowers like lilies.//They bloom in more than one season… Summer and Fall, if I’m not mistaken.
You can get to know people very well by just letting them talk.//People tend to like talking about themselves if you let them.
I’ve gained a lot of knowledge and insight into who people are by doing that.
Favorite video game genre? Hmm… Hard question. I like action-adventure video games.//<portrait=happy>They let me travel to a different world whenever I want.
It’s escapism, so to speak.//<portrait=happy>Even if you have a great life, it’s still fun to explore the underworld or the galaxy sometimes, don’t you think?
Are you going to the beach or heading back home?
Nothing much… I’m building up my portfolio. Who knows? One of these pictures might land me a gig.
There sure are a lot of mosquitoes here. I think the heat just makes them worse.
It also makes me crave fruit tarts. Hmm…//The heat...not the mosquitos.
I had the worst night last night. I think <NPCName>Valentina</>'s dad came to visit, and he was so loud in the lobby. I didn’t sleep very well afterward… Kept waking up, you know?
Oh, well. It’s a small price to pay to live in a society. I could live in the middle of nowhere like <NPCName>Emma</> and <NPCName>Dippa</>, but I choose not to.
This goes without saying, but please don’t tell anyone. I don’t want to make a fuss over nothing.
I’m getting along great with the girls at the inn. You know them too, right?
I think I’ll make pizza tomorrow for all the girls at the inn. It’ll be nice to catch up before the new week starts, I think.
Nothing’s set in stone yet, though. For starters, I don’t even have any cheese.
Spring colors are gorgeous here.//It’s my time to farm photos!
I think my favorite place to take photos in Spring is around the lake.//<portrait=blushing>The old temple just looks beautiful surrounded by cherry blossoms.
Oh wow, it’s Spring already!//I’m excited to take <NPCName>Stephen</> out again and show him around.
I like to take photos of the leaves as they grow. It’s beautiful and poetic, you know?//Yeah! It <Italic>does</> show progression.
<NPCName>Mr. Mayor</> hires me to document the festivals. He pays me pretty well.//Let’s see, up next is the Cherry Blossom Festival on the 10th…
There’s a new <Italic>Resident Vile</> game coming out this Summer.//I don’t think I’ll get it, though… No time to play.//I think I’ll just watch someone stream it or something.
Besides, I don’t think it’ll be on consoles yet.//My laptop isn’t powerful enough to run it smoothly. Heh heh!
The Summer photos of Coral Island are pretty popular. I mean that’s what you usually want to see from an island, right?//<portrait=blushing>Cheerful Summer vibes!

I’m so glad I live near the beach. I can take <NPCName>Stephen</> out whenever I want, and I can take beautiful sunset and sunrise photos every day.//Granted, I don’t do it, but I could if I wanted to!
Oh, <NPCName>Stephen</> loves Summer! He’s always so happy when I take him for walks on the beach.
I like wearing boots. I know the weather is a bit…hot, but they give me great support for walking.//So I don’t accidentally stumble on some rock and fall while I’m holding the camera.
I wish it wasn’t so humid.
I know you can make fruit tarts whenever, but it always feels like a Summer dish to me.
I do like taking beach photos in Summer. Is that too basic?
Oh wow, it’s Summer already! That means we’re gonna have a community beach cleanup soon. Should I take <NPCName>Stephen</> with me? Hmm…
Would it be okay if I take photos of you during the community beach cleanup?//I take photos for the event… Just wanna make sure I have your consent.
Pizza is food for all seasons.//Chilly Winter night? Good! Hot Summer like today? Very good!
I think Fall is just so pretty, no matter where you are.//<portrait=happy>But on Coral Island? It’s on another level.

I’d say one of the hardest things about taking photos in Fall is getting the right composition.//<portrait=concerned>If I don’t do it right, all I get is different shades of brown. That’s a boring photo.
I don’t have a favorite season.//I think Coral Island is a beautiful place, no matter what time of year… That’s why I moved here.
There’s so many fun activities at the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=surprised>And so many fun things to take photos of!
I like taking photos of <NPCName>Stephen</> in Fall. His blue shell stands out so beautifully in the Fall colors.
Oh wow, it’s Fall already! The island is going to look so pretty with the orange leaves.
I can’t take <NPCName>Stephen</> for walks in Winter. It’s kind of sad, but he doesn’t like the cold.

I have <NPCName>Stephen</>'s tank heated during Winter. He’s a lot more lively when the water is warmer.//I wanna get one of those smart thermometers for fish tanks, but they cost too much… So, the manual one will do for now.
Coral Island is always beautiful, no matter the season.//<portrait=blushing>In Winter, the snow blankets everything and turns it into this serene, otherworldly island.

Sometimes I worry something’s wrong with <NPCName>Stephen</>, but then I remember it’s Winter, and he’s just going to be less active than usual.//Do you think I should have <NPCName>Yuri</> check him out?//Can she even…?
It's cold…but I like to wear shorts.//I move easier in them. You could say they’re less restricting.
Oh wow, it’s Winter already! No wonder <NPCName>Stephen</> looks a bit lethargic.
Every time I take a photo of the island in Winter, I think “Winter Wonderland.” It really is a wonder!
I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. I think it’s one of the advantages of this line of work.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood…always.
I’m starting to feel the heat.//And mosquito bites.
If you pay close attention to your surroundings, you can spot wild animals on the island.
Birds’ nests are always nice to spot. This one time, I took progress pictures of eggs in a nest until they hatched.
It took quite a while, but it was worth it.
Harvest season is coming up, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re about to get really busy, aren’t you?
I’m going to take it easy today. I’m still so tired from the beach cleanup.
We don’t have anything going on until the third week of Fall.
Umm…the Harvest Festival on the fifteenth is the next one.
Can you believe it’s the eleventh already? Winter is literally right around the corner.
Oh my… I need to find my coat. It snows pretty hard here.
If my mom found out I was wearing shorts on a windy day like this, I’d be in deep trouble. He-he!
Anything cool going on today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Get it? ’Cause it’s Winter… Cool…//<portrait=blushing>Heh heh!
A lot of cool things happen here in Winter.
The Winter Fair is on the twenty-first, for one.
Oops, I mean the twentieth… My, oh my… I’m really excited.
Are you planting anything this Winter?
Whoa, it’s a busy year for you. Must be tiring to be farming all year round.

Special.SourceString: Yeah, farming like usual, except in the cold.

Text.SourceString: That’s great, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s good to take a break once in a while and just enjoy this island. After all, isn’t that why we’re all here?

Special.SourceString: Nah, I’ll farm again in the spring.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Eva</> and I wanted to throw a simple party for the twin's birthday tomorrow, but they said no because the New Year’s Eve party’s in two days.
Oh, well…
<NPCName>Erika</> is good at cutting curly hair.//She's the one taking care of mine.
I’ll just wait until the rain calms down a bit and take more photographs then.
It looks quite muddy out there. I don’t wanna slip and fall.
Hmm… What should I have for dinner?
I feed <NPCName>Stephen</> twice a day…//I wanna make sure he gets all the nutrients he needs, but I don’t want to accidentally overfeed him.
Can you hold one sec? I’m in a boss battle.
Oh my… It’s storming really hard.
The wind is a bit scary, isn’t it?
To be honest, I’m a bit concerned about this storm.//It’s been windy all day, and the deck isn’t exactly brand new.
*nervous laughter*
I pay yearly at the inn.//They give me a really good rate, and I take photographs for them for free.
The photos cost me close to nothing, so living here is dirt cheap at the end of the day.
The sand can be scorching on bare feet.
This beach is where I found <NPCName>Stephen</>… Right over there, in fact!//He lost a claw, so I’m providing him a safe place to regrow it.
I search the beach every so often for injured animals.//Fortunately, I haven’t found any besides <NPCName>Stephen</> so far.
Interesting question… <NPCName>Stephen</> is a male lobster. I’m pretty sure.
<NPCName>Kenny</> and I checked. <NPCName>Stephen</>'s first pair of swimmerets are pointy, so he’s a male.//Females have thin and feathery swimmerets.
[<NPCName>Macy</> is dancing.]
I come here when I feel like treating myself to a home-cooked meal and cold drinks.
I was told <NPCName>Frank</> cooks everything on the menu himself.
Why would you wanna cook if you can get someone to do it for you, right?
It’s much warmer here than at the inn.
It’s much warmer here than at the inn.
It’s much warmer here than at the inn.
There are plenty of nature and photography books here for inspiration.
There’s information about farming and fishing too, isn’t there?
You can nap here, and as long as you don’t snore, I think you can get away with it.
<NPCName>Stephen</> sure loves his tank… I spent my monthly grocery budget building that.//<portrait=happy>I lived by foraging and scavenging for the whole month.
Just like university years.
I thought about becoming a farmer too, but I couldn’t see myself committing to staying in one spot for such a long time.
I don’t get too stressed thankfully. I think it’s one of the advantages of this line of work.//I'm always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood…always.
Do you feel a gust of wind? It’s making me feel sleepy.
Where’s the wind coming from anyway? Hmm…
Getting here is an exercise by itself.
I had a big bowl of avocado for breakfast this morning.//<portrait=happy>What did you have?
I used to work for a corporation, dealing with financial records, before I decided to try my luck at photography.
I love it so far. I get to meet people with interesting stories and take pretty pictures of nature.
Other interests? Uh. Um. I like video games! And I like people. And I like my rescue lobster, <NPCName>Stephen</>!
Hm. That’s not a lot, huh? It’s probably fine. Work-life balance is overrated.
Degrees and certificates aren’t everything. They help when you’re starting out, but I never took more than a few photography classes.
I actually have a degree in finance! Funny, right?
This island is so beautiful. It’s hard to take a bad photo!
Not that every picture I take here is a winner. Composition matters too. But still!
<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>.
Just memorizing your name! I read somewhere it helps to repeat someone’s name while you look at their face.
Do you have any photography experience, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Hey, that’s fine!

Special.SourceString: Just selfies and such, nothing impressive.

Text.SourceString: Amazing! I, like, never get to geek out about framing and cool lenses and stuff except on the internet.
Ha ha! Don’t worry, I do too. But that doesn’t mean you can’t learn to love taking them!

Special.SourceString: I hate even being in pictures, so…

Text.SourceString: Hold on. I just spotted an AMAZING shot!
Blah. I need more caffeine.
Our world really is beautiful. Preserving that beauty is a worthwhile pursuit.
My weekly walks with <NPCName>Stephen</> are important. He really seems to enjoy them.
What is it?
Coral Island has some neat local legends. I wonder which of ’em are true.
I need a lot of space. My freedom is important to me.
Do you ever miss your family back home? It’s nice to be free, but I still miss my parents.
You’re…in my way. Move, please.
Oh, <NPCName>Stephen</> is my only pet. Any others, and I’d worry myself half to death!
How goes the farming? Is it <Italic>farmy</>?
Do ya like video games? It’s hard to find anybody these days who doesn’t at least play games on their phone.
I’m not a hardcore gamer or anything, but I love indie games! They inspire me a lot.
Being a photographer means I have to be ready to whip out my camera at a moment’s notice.
There’ve been dozens, if not hundreds, of shots that got away. They haunt me, <PlayerName>$player</>. They haunt me.
Living on such a small island is weird. You eventually know everything about everyone.
I guess you can also say it’s nice… Intimate, maybe?
I wouldn’t say I have any particularly close friends. But I’m not a loner, either.
You know what’s funny? I don’t like raw fruit, but I love, love, love baked fruit.
It’s a sensory thing! I just hate the texture of uncooked fruit, but once you bake it? Hoo!
Can you cook? Well, you’re a farmer; I’m sure you can. I can’t, though!
I’ve worked hard to give <NPCName>Stephen</> a good life.//Once he regrows his claw, though, I’ll return him to the wild.
Mmm… I could really go for a snack right now.
Pretty much everyone in town has given me permission to take pictures of them.
There are a few exceptions! All for good reasons.
Most of my work so far has been nature photography, so I’m really good at framing that specific type of shot.
I’m wondering if I should expand my work to other things, though.//<portrait=annoyed>What if it gets boring? Buh!
If it’s one goose, two geese…why not one moose, two meese? I’m so confused.
Do you like to dance, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I do!//It’s great to let your energy out sometimes, even if you look goofy.
My best pictures all play with composition in unexpected ways.//One of my favorites is of a bird of paradise, looking all regal.
But if you look in the corner, you can see a cat with huge eyes, creeping up on him!
I got the shot just in time. I lowered my camera, and the bird shrieked and took flight!//<portrait=normal>It was hysterical.
I hope <NPCName>Stephen</>'s okay. Well, I’m sure he is, but I still worry.
It can take some time before you figure out what you want to do in life. It did for both of us, right?
I was working a corporate job like you for a while before I became a photographer!
I had the weirdest dream last night. I was a pickle, and everyone was standing around me, laughing.
People always expect you to be constantly friendly and upbeat.//It’s exhausting.
I try to be friendly, but I want it to be on my terms!
Chocolate sounds great right now.//<portrait=happy>I’d love some hot chocolate.
I had a video call with my parents today. They were happy to see me, and I was happy to see them.
Drinking coffee takes too long. Maybe I should just snort instant espresso powder.
I’m kidding! I’m kidding!
Half the time when I make a joke, people assume I’m serious. I wonder why…
I like coming here just to think about things. The ocean clears my head.
Don’tcha just love that sea-salt scent? Ha! That’s fun to say. Sea-salt scent!
I love the dim lights here. I can handle loud noises just fine; it’s my eyes that are too sensitive.
There are some awesome photo books here. <NPCName>Millie</> got some just for me! She’s a real doll.
Hmm, how do I frame this… Landscape or portrait?
Hang on, I need to change my lens.
The light on the sea is perfect. <PlayerName>$player</>, look at that!
Buh! The sun is so bright today, it hurts my eyes! But it’s such good lighting for photography…
My head hurts… It’s the light. Ugh.
You can get some really compelling shots in the rain… other times, it’s just kinda drab.
It’s so cold out there! I’d bundle up a little more if I were you.
So much snow! Wish I had taller boots. My socks are getting soaked.
When it storms, it literally goes all day. How do the clouds not run out of water?
I bet I could get some awesome lightning shots if I were patient enough! But I’m tired…
